                        <h1>The Map of Polish Bloggers</h1>
                    </header>
                    <p><strong>Blog Forum Gdańsk</strong> is an interdisciplinary conference, which takes place in Gdańsk every year since
2010. In 2012 the main topic of the conference were practical skills which come along with from blogging.</p>
                    <h3>I mapped polish blogosphere</h3>
                    <p>Organizing Committee of Blog Forum Gdańsk had definitely challenged me. My task was to create an infographic which shows most popular polish bloggers. They were selected on the basis of the analysis prepared using the tools by Brand 24 and Sotrender. I dedicated long hours of my conceptual and design projecting work to this task. I decided to portray bloggers as individuals who lived on thematically selected islands. The final map consist of 6 big and 10 little islands floating on Yotube Mare. They are as follow: The Lifestyle Island inhabited by 14 bloggers, Hobby Island, of 4 people, 3 people living on Facebook Island, 13 on Technology Island, 2 in Corporate Land and 4 in Political Jungle.</p>
                    <h3>Designing in a good taste</h3>
                    <p>Every blogger has his own icon with his image, which is located on his part of the island as a geotag. I have done my best to capture characteristically features of each of them. In addition I designed pictograms for each area of the island. The Peninsula of Apple is symbolized with characteristic half - bite apple with monocle, The Gorge of Culinary is depicted with Mr. Pot, who evade his lid like a hat. I created 19 graphics of this type. Adding the50 portrays of bloggers, give us 69 unique icons altogether.</p>
                    <h3>summary</h3>
                    <footer>
