                        <h1>Consequently for Gdańsk</h1>
                    </header>
                    <p>I was asked by <strong>Gdańsk City Hall</strong> to prepare materials, which in an easy and interesting way tell the story of positive changes and improvements that have been introduced in the city during past two years. I carefully analyzed possible ways of presenting that material and I have chosen infographics as the most suitable and viewer-friendly form…<a href="http://www.adamowicz.pl/infografiki" target="_blank">See how they look like!</a>.</p>
                    <h3>Big changes in an attractive form</h3>
                    <p>At first, I felt overwhelmed with the amount of information as I received 32-pages long report. My priority was to find lucid and attractive way to communicate with citizens of Gdańsk. I converted a large number of text, tables and data into a modern form of infographics.</p>
                    <h3>The creation is not always easy</h3>
                    <p>I decided to divide the materials into four thematic parts and assigned particular city changes and achievements to each of them. Projects and ideas were briefly consulted with President’s Office during the whole process. As a result of our mutual cooperation we distinguished four areas of city development: commuting, recreation and sport, development and life & city.</p>
                    <h3>The effect – readable and friendly massage</h3>
                    <p>As the result I made four infographics, which in clear and interesting way show how the city council actions brought changes to Gdańsk. Each infographic illustrates particular goals depicted by attractive and colorful graphics and icons. Moreover, they are supported with dedicated slogans for each thematic part.</p>
                    <h3>summary</h3>
                    <footer>
                    	<div>
                        	<p>I designed</p>
