                        <h1>Creative Cities</h1>
                    </header>
                    <p><strong>Creative Cities</strong> is a project carried out by Gdańsk Entrepreneurship Foundation in cooperation with Gdańsk City Hall. Its aim is to integrate local, creative entrepreneurships and to create a space fordevelopment and experience exchange. Based on the summaries I received on many meetings, I made an infographic which sums up the project.</p>
                    <h3>Numbers don’t have to be boring</h3>
                    <p>Reports I got from organizers had many numbers and statics. I have decided to deal with the project with my intrinsic sense of humor and illustrated for exmaple - how many sandwiches were eaten by participants, how many chairs were used, how much coffee they drank. I presented statistics using icons to visualize character of the meetings. I displayed range of the project on a simplified map of Europe, which helps imagine the distance between the cities. Local character of the project is highlighted by the background of infographic which displays contours of characteristic Old Town buildings in Gdańsk.</p>
                    <h3>summary</h3>
                    <footer>
                    	<div>
                        	<p>I visualized</p>
                            <strong>38</strong>
                            <p>numbers</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                        	<p>I designed</p>
                            <strong>19</strong>
                            <p>icons</p>
                        </div>
