                <li class="startpeople">
                	<header>
                    	<div class="preview">
                        	<div class="nano">
                            <div class="content">
                    		<img src="images/content/start.jpg" width="970" height="2280" />
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h1>Student’s Run to Career</h1>
                    </header>
                    <p><strong>Start People - Work and Personal Consultancy Agency,</strong> asked me to design infographic, which illustrates students’ demands for labour market. An infographic visualize extensive data gathered by Start People as a result of the survey conducted among students of public universities in Gdańsk and Łódź.</p>
                    <h3>They are separated by 334 km, but do they have separate labour market demands?</h3>
                    <p>I received two reports full of figures, which together had 40 slides with tables and statistics. Fortunately, analysis and synthesis are my strong sides. Thanks to them and with help of icons and pictograms I succeeded in designing readable and simply message as infographic. I took into account the most important facts, which I divided in nine thematic categories. I illustrated differences with an image of female student, who is “with one feet in Gdańsk, and one in Łódź”. I wanted to highlight two different point of views with looks and outfit. These students are not only 334 km distant from each other, but also vary in life choices. For example, students from Gdańsk more often choose technical faculties, whereas students from Łódź choose social – economical faculties.</p>
                    <h3>Readable and colorful</h3>
                    <p>A range of icons and graphics make illustrations more diverse, thus helping the viewer to understand the message and information. At first glance one can see what they have in common and what is different for the students from these two cities. The whole design is maintained in pastel colors to please both young and elder recipients. It was used to promote Conference Start HR: “Students’ run for career – a sprint or a marathon?” organized by Start People in Gdańsk and Łódź in April 2012.</p>
                    <h3>summary</h3>
