                            <div class="content">
                    		<img src="images/content/student.jpg" width="970" height="3298" />
                            </div>
                            </div>  
                        </div>
                        <h1>Students is also a customer</h1>
                    </header>
                    <p>Universities which enter the competition for students should invest in good trainer, because dark clouds are gathering above them. To make long story short, according to forecasts demographic decrease will take down private higher education and devalue public universities by 2020.</p>
                    <h3>Data, statistics, reports</h3>
                    <p>Largest Polish daily journal, “Gazeta Wyborcza” published an article which inspired me to verify the forecasts about the condition of Polish higher education system. I prepared an infographic based on statistical yearbooks from GUS (Central Statistical Office), data from Ministry of Science and Higher Education, reports from Economic Research Institute, Ernst &Young Business Advisory and media materials. It shows universities, their values and brands form marketing perspective. In result, analysis of abovementioned sources makes a picture of present and future conditions on academic market.</p>
                    <h3>University is also a brand</h3>
                    <p>The aim of designing this infographic was to show the influence of demographic decline on public and private higher education institutions and encourage people to take up public debate. Competition for students, best lectures, investors and donors should become a base for building strong and recognizable brands. As a result of planned and well-considered actions Polish universities
can also create trustworthy brands. An example of good university branding are universities in Western Europe which invest in themselves as well as their students.</p>
